Class Meal

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • classes.Meal

  • public class Meal
extends java.util.Observable
    This class represents the meals that are on offer in the restaurant. A meal has a name, a price, and a list of ingredients. If the meal is on a special offer, its special price has to be specified.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Meal

        public Meal(java.lang.String name,
            double price)
        This constructor initializes the creation of a meal. The ingredients still need to be added. By default, the special price is set as equal to the normal price.
        Parameters:
        name - The meal's name. It's the main characteristic of the meal and will be used to refer to it.
        price - The price of the meal. This price is set by the chef.

      • Meal

        public Meal(java.lang.String name,
            double price,
            boolean isOnlySpecial)
        This constructor initializes the creation of a special offer meal. The ingredients still need to be added.
        Parameters:
        name - The meal's name. It's the main characteristic of the meal and will be used to refer to it.
        price - The price of the meal. This price is set by the chef.
        isOnlySpecial - Set to true is the meal is created through the insertOffer method.
